				<h1></h1>Dear parents,<p></p>
<div class="edit">
<p dir="ltr">The last week has been a whirlwind with respect to the coronavirus developments and their impact on the school. You should know, the amount of work that has happened behind the scenes has been very impressive. We have an amazing staff and they have done great work in a very short period of time.  Since Monday, they’ve:</p>
<ul>
<li dir="ltr"><p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Completed a needs analysis  </p></li>
<li dir="ltr"><p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Created new policies on school attendance</p></li>
<li dir="ltr"><p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Reviewed and adjusted cleaning procedures</p></li>
<li dir="ltr"><p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Developed an action plan to respond to an array of potential scenarios</p></li>
<li dir="ltr"><p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Developed a distance learning plan that includes teacher expectations, a technology assessment, platform selection. </p></li>
<li dir="ltr"><p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Conducted teacher training on distance learning technology</p></li>
<li dir="ltr"><p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Established reporting metrics for communication with the county health department. </p></li>
</ul>
<p dir="ltr">While there are aspects of our plan that are still underdevelopment, we have the critical pieces in place to successfully manage this situation moving forward and I’d like to recognize the following individuals for their excellent work this week.</p>
<p dir="ltr">Shelby Dieters, Dean of Instruction</p>
<p dir="ltr">Stephanie Avery, Dean of Students and Families</p>
<p dir="ltr">Patti Davis, Business Manager</p>
<p dir="ltr">Amanda Barbosa, First Grade Teacher and Teacher Coach</p>
<p dir="ltr">Ashley Doyle, Executive Assistant</p>
<p dir="ltr">The school is in great hands and I am proud to work with the faculty and staff here at Renaissance Academy.</p>
<p dir="ltr">Best regards,</p>
<p dir="ltr">Mark Ursic</p>
<p dir="ltr">Executive Director</p>
</div>
<p></p>
